Region Counsel V
01 May 2014 04:34 PM - UAE
 Manages the development of legal strategies for local or regional
senior management, including leading high value/risk commercial
transactions and program review, drafting, and negotiation.
 Develops and recommends innovative process improvements to
effectively address business needs of an aligned country or region.
 Identifies and resolves highly complex local/regional legal,
regulatory, and business issues.
 Manages legal responsibilities for multiple client organizations
with divergent priorities and needs.
 Leads complex, multidimensional projects or transactions.
 May act as sole country counsel; serves as the primary legal contact
for local or regional management and coordinates activity with
corporate, regional, and other country resources.
 Acts as a master of the local/regional environment by advising on
complex laws and regulations and their implications for the
local/regional operations/businesses.
 Provides strategic legal counseling to management at a country,
region, or business unit level.
 May act as sole Country Counsel in a country with a moderately
complex business mix, such as where revenue is largely derived from
direct and indirect product sales from multiple businesses, and
non-sales functions require legal support.
 May provide specialized legal expertise in one or more areas of
strategic importance or having a significant impact on HP's revenue or
risk level.
